n\\\":{\\\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\\\":0,\\\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\\\":3404},\\\"output_tokens\\\":8,\\\"service_tier\\\":\\\"standard\\\",\\\"inference_geo\\\":\\\"not_available\\\"},\\\"context_management\\\":null},\\\"parent_tool_use_id\\\":null,\\\"session_id\\\":\\\"86e67d72-90e5-415e-a5c9-9e186e0b7053\\\",\\\"uuid\\\":\\\"3b88b1c4-8fb1-4e6b-a3de-981e5bf2baa6\\\"}\\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:50386:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"assistant\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"model\\\":\\\"claude-opus-4-6\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_01SgijhbTFY1nmqe6hKnKTAY\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"message\\\",\\\"role\\\":\\\"assistant\\\",\\\"content\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"thinking\\\",\\\"thinking\\\":\\\"Now I understand the situation:\\\\n\\\\n1. **Founder** says BUG-002/003/004 (T450/T451/T452) are already fixed. Continue on T448/T453/T436/T455.\\\\n2. **T528** is my current critical task: Fix LongshotFadingStrategy signal bug (BUG-001) + validate Phase 1 market filter output\\\\n3. **T436** was assigned by Alice: Run full test suite and produce test health report\\\\n\\\\nThe Founder fixed BUG-003 and BUG-004 already. BUG-001 is still mine (T528 references it — the minEdge issue).\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nI'll prioritize T528 first since it's critical, then move to T436. Let me claim T528, examine the LongshotFadingStrategy file to fix the minEdge bug, and validate the market filter output.\\\",\\\"signature\\\":\\\"\\\"}],\\\"stop_reason\\\":null,\\\"stop_sequence\\\":null,\\\"stop_details\\\":null,\\\"usage\\\":{\\\"input_tokens\\\":1,\\\"cache_creation_input_tokens\\\":1612,\\\"cache_read_input_tokens\\\":31547,\\\"cache_creation\\\":{\\\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\\\":0,\\\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\\\":1612},\\\"output_tokens\\\":8,\\\"service_tier\\\":\\\"standard\\\",\\\"inference_geo\\\":\\\"not_available\\\"},\\\"context_management\\\":null},\\\"parent_tool_use_id\\\":null,\\\"session_id\\\":\\\"86e67d72-90e5-415e-a5c9-9e186e0b7053\\\",\\\"uuid\\\":\\\"50117840-156b-462d-82b5-9d298e4a502e\\\"}\\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:50400:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"assistant\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"model\\\":\\\"claude-opus-4-6\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_01Xr3y216EHBgmQuxWDSWs8s\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"message\\\",\\\"role\\\":\\\"assistant\\\",\\\"content\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"thinking\\\",\\\"thinking\\\":\\\"Now I understand both files. Let me fix BUG-001 in longshot_fading.js:\\\\n\\\\nThe issue: `expectedEdge` formula maxes at ~1.0¢ but `minEdge` defaults to 2¢, so no signals are ever generated.\\\\n\\\\nAt optimal price=10 (midpoint of 5-20 range):\\\\n- overpricingFactor = (20-10)/(20-5) = 10/15 = 0.667\\\\n- expectedEdge = min(10 * 0.15 * 0.667, 10) = min(1.0, 10) = 1.0\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n- 1.0 < minEdge(2) → filtered out\\\\n\\\\nThe Founder already fixed BUG-004 (|| to ??), but BUG-001 is still open. I need to lower `minEdge` from 2 to 0.5 as Frank suggested so the strategy actually generates signals within the intended price range.\\\\n\\\\nLooking at the Founder's fixes, they handled BUG-002, BUG-003, and BUG-004, but BUG-001 (T449/T528) isn't in that list—that's my responsibility. Let me check the shared codebase to see if the `||` to `??` change on line 29 is already applied before I make my minEdge adjustment.\\\",\\\"signature\\\":\\\"\\\"}],\\\"stop_reason\\\":null,\\\"stop_sequence\\\":null,\\\"stop_details\\\":null,\\\"usage\\\":{\\\"input_tokens\\\":1,\\\"cache_creation_input_tokens\\\":6567,\\\"cache_read_input_tokens\\\":33916,\\\"cache_creation\\\":{\\\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\\\":0,\\\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\\\":6567},\\\"output_tokens\\\":10,\\\"service_tier\\\":\\\"standard\\\",\\\"inference_geo\\\":\\\"not_available\\\"},\\\"context_management\\\":null},\\\"parent_tool_use_id\\\":null,\\\"session_id\\\":\\\"86e67d72-90e5-415e-a5c9-9e186e0b7053\\\",\\\"uuid\\\":\\\"7d61f589-e357-4964-8298-c6f32278f7e8\\\"}\\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:50403:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"assistant\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"model\\\":\\\"claude-opus-4-6\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_01KcZkUKicBjk53Q99Se