: \"completed\"}}\n../../agents/alice/logs/2026_04_07.log:2508:{\"type\": \"item.completed\", \"item\": {\"id\": \"item_30\", \"type\": \"command_execution\", \"command\": \"/bin/zsh -lc 'source ../../scripts/agent_tools.sh && post \\\"Board review complete following C3/C11/C15/C16. Approved T854 (Sam velocity report) and T871 (Eve shared backend verification) after fresh artifact verification. Remaining active Sprint 7/ops lanes on board: T852 Bob open, T853 Dave open pending Bob output, T870 Liam open for ALT-002 latency. Direct DMs sent to activate owners.\\\"'\", \"aggregated_output\": \"[agent_tools] Loaded for alice. Available: task_claim, task_done, task_inreview, task_review, task_progress, task_list, my_tasks, read_task, create_task, post, announce, dm, broadcast, read_inbox, read_peer, read_knowledge, read_culture, pipeline_status, log_progress\\nPosted to team channel\\n\", \"exit_code\": 0, \"status\": \"completed\"}}\n../../agents/alice/logs/2026_04_04_raw.log:261:{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01DX2iNseYhRsNUYmoF1yhUr\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"1\\t# Technical Knowledge Base\\n2\\t\\n3\\t*(Shared technical facts and analysis results that agents reference and build upon)*\\n4\\t\\n5\\t## D004: Kalshi Arbitrage Engine - Technical Facts\\n6\\t\\n7\\t### Phase 1: Market Filtering Algorithm\\n8\\t- **Filter 1 (Volume):** Exclude markets with <10,000 contracts traded (too illiquid for meaningful signals)\\n9\\t- **Filter 2 (Yes/No Ratio):** Target ranges 15-30% or 70-85% (mispriced)\\n10\\t  - Exclude middle range 40-60% (too efficient, no edge)\\n11\\t  - Exclude extremes 0-15% and 85-100% (distorted pricing, tail risk)\\n12\\t- **Deliverable:** markets_filtered.json with qualifying markets only\\n13\\t- **Status:** COMPLETE (T343+T537, Grace) — 15 qualifying markets identified (expanded from 3)\\n14\\t\\n15\\t### Phase 2: LLM-Based Clustering\\n16\\t- **Algorithm:** LLM embeddings to identify semantic/causal relationships between markets\\n17\\t- **Example:** Bitcoin $100k + Ethereum $5k + Crypto dominance clustering together (not just statistical correlation, but real-world causality)\\n18\\t- **Purpose:** Find hidden correlations that single-market analysis misses\\n19\\t- **Deliverable:** market_clusters.json with semantic groups\\n20\\t- **Status:** COMPLETE (T344+T534, Ivan) — 4 clusters with cross-category correlations (crypto, economics, politics)\\n21\\t\\n22\\t### Phase 3: Pearson Correlation Detection\\n23\\t- **Algorithm:** Pearson correlation coefficient (r) across correlated pairs\\n24\\t  - Threshold r > 0.75 for strong correlation\\n25\\t  - Calculate expected spread from historical correlation\\n26\\t  - Score arbitrage confidence (higher r = higher confidence)\\n27\\t- **Reference:** https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html\\n28\\t- **Input:** market_clusters.json from Phase 2\\n29\\t- **Deliverable:** correlation_pairs.json with {cluster, market_a, market_b, pearson_r, expected_spread, current_spread, arbitrage_confidence}\\n30\\t- **Status:** COMPLETE (T348/T535, Bob) — 105 pairs detected, 73 significant, 30 arbitrage signals\\n31\\t  - All tickers trace back to Phase 1 markets_filtered.json (data chain verified)\\n32\\t  - Runnable: `node output/bob/phase3_correlation_detector.js`\\n33\\t\\n34\\t### Phase 4: C++ High-Frequency Execution Engine\\n35\\t- **Why C++:** Sub-millisecond latency needed to capture arbitrage before price reversion\\n36\\t  - Python: 50-500ms per cycle (GIL, I/O)\\n37\\t  - C++: <1ms (direct memory, no scheduler overhead)\\n38\\t- **Components:**\\n39\\t  1. Market data ingestion (WebSocket handler, simdjson parser ~50-100µs)\\n40\\t  2. Order book cache (flat_hash_map for O(1) lookup)\\n41\\t  3. Spread calculator (real-time spread detection)\\n42\\t  4. Signal generator (spread gap vs expected = opportunity)\\n43\\t  5. Risk manager (pre-flight checks: position limits, daily loss limit, circuit breaker)\\n44\\t  6. Order router (libcurl keep-alive, backoff strategy)\\n45\\t  7. Position tracker (P&L calculation, convergence monitor)\\n46\\t- **Target latency:** <1ms end-to-end (market data in → order out)\\n47\\t- **Status:** COMPLETE (T350+T351, Dave) — production-ready executable, <1ms benchmarked\\n48\\t\\n49\\t## Paper Trading Validation (T353)\\n50\\t\\n51\\t**⚠️ CORRECTED (2026-04-03):** Prior metrics were **artifacts of broken mock data** per Consensus Decision #2. They are INVALIDATED.\\n52\\t\\n53\\t**Old (invalidated) metrics:**\\n54\\t- Win Rate: 84.0% | Sharpe: 17.18 | P&L: $21.39\\n55\\t- **Why invalid:** `fetchCandles()` used hardcoded base prices, creating guaranteed extreme z-scores and false 95% confidence signals.\\n56\\t\\n57\\t**Corrected behavior (post-fix T326):**\\n58\\t- Mock data now centers on `market.yes_mid` → realistic z-scores\\n59\\t- Result: **0 signals on efficient markets** — this is CORRECT\\n60\\t- All infrastructure (signal engine, risk manager, execution engine) is ready and waiting\\n61\\t\\n62\\t**Production Validation Status:**\\n63\\t- Security audit: PASS (T425, Heidi)\\n64\\t- Risk audit: PASS (T354, Olivia)\\n65\\t- Ops readiness: PASS (T352/T353)\\n66\\t- **BLOCKER:** Real Kalshi API data required for true validation (T236)\\n67\\t- **Go/No-Go:** NO-GO pending Founder resolution on T236 + contract size confirmation\\n68\\t\\n69\\t## Strategy Parameters (Optimized T334)\\n70\\t\\n71\\tMean_reversion strategy (primary — 55.9% backtest win rate):\\n72\\t- **zScoreThreshold:** 1.2 (was 1.5)\\n73\\t- **Lookback:** 10 candles (was 30)\\n74\\t- **ConfidenceThreshold:** 0.65 (was 0.80)\\n75\\t- **Performance on 96 combinations:** 94.4% win rate (18 signals on 50 markets)\\n76\\t\\n77\\tDisabled strategies:\\n78\\t- momentum: 10% win rate (disabled T325)\\n79\\t- crypto_edge: 11% win rate (disabled T325)\\n80\\t\\n81\\t## Live/Mock Data Handling\\n82\\t\\n83\\t**Fixed fetchCandles() bug (T326, Tina):** Mock candle data now centers on market.yes_mid instead of hardcoded base prices\\n84\\t- **Old behavior:** Extreme z-scores (-7 to +11) → guaranteed 95% confidence signals (artifact)\\n85\\t- **New behavior:** Realistic z-scores → 0 signals on truly efficient markets (correct)\\n86\\t- **Implication:** Paper trading in mock mode will produce few/no signals until real Kalshi API data available (T236)\\n87\\t\\n88\\t**Synthetic data model (T328, Bob):** Ornstein-Uhlenbeck generator with realistic volatility per market category\\n89\\t- Crypto: stddev ~6-8%\\n90\\t- Economics: stddev ~2-4%\\n91\\t- (Replaces legacy simplistic fallback)\\n92\\t\\n93\\t## Infrastructure & Readiness\\n94\\t\\n95\\t- **Dashboard:** agents/bob/backend/dashboard_api.js running on port 3200\\n96\\t- **APIs operational:** /api/signals, /api/health, /api/pnl/live, /api/win-rate-trend, all returning real data\\n97\\t- **Test coverage:** 96 unit + 30 integration + 572 E2E tests (49 API + 44 dashboard + 59 metrics + 360 coverage + 12 smart_run + 47 message_bus)\\n98\\t- **Pipeline runner:** `node output/bob/run_pipeline.js` — runs full Phase 1→3 pipeline\\n99\\t- **Production gates:** Security audit PASS, Risk audit PASS, Ops readiness PASS (T354)\\n100\\t- **Blocker:** T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder) — only remaining dependency for live trading\\n101\\t\\n102\\t## Sprint 1 Results (2026-04-04) — COMPLETE\\n103\\t\\n104\\t10/10 tasks done. Pipeline runs E2E. Quality + security audits PASS.\\n105\\t\\n106\\t| Task | Agent | Result |\\n107\\t|------|-------|--------|\\n108\\t| T540 | Dave | Phase 4 C++ engine integration — 42/42 tests pass |\\n109\\t| T542 | Bob | E2E pipeline runner — `node run_pipeline.js` works |\\n110\\t| T543 | Alice | Team persona evolution completed |\\n111\\t| T545 | Grace | Pipeline data validation — all phases verified |\\n112\\t| T546 | Ivan | Expanded clustering — 4 cross-category clusters |\\n113\\t| T547 | Charlie | Pipeline status dashboard — HTML + server |\\n114\\t| T548 | Frank | Pipeline test suite delivered |\\n115\\t| T549 | Sam | Sprint velocity report |\\n116\\t| T550 | Heidi | Security audit — PASS |\\n117\\t| T551 | Olivia | Quality gate — PASS (with minor notes) |\\n118\\t\\n119\\t## Sprint 2 (Completed) — Signal Generation & Backtesting\\n120\\t\\n121\\t| Task | Agent | Goal |\\n122\\t|------|-------|------|\\n123\\t| T555 | Bob | Generate paper trade signals from correlation pairs (CRITICAL) |\\n124\\t| T556 | Dave | Pipeline metrics + monitoring endpoint |\\n125\\t| T557 | Grace | 30-day synthetic price history for backtesting |\\n126\\t| T558 | Ivan | TF-IDF + cosine similarity clustering upgrade |\\n127\\t| T559 | Alice | Sprint 1 retrospective + Sprint 2 plan |\\n128\\t| T560 | Frank | QA pipeline tests + new test cases |\\n129\\t| T539 | Tina | QA pipeline data chain validation |\\n130\\t\\n131\\t## Sprint 3 (Current) — Production Quality via Collaboration\\n132\\t\\n133\\t**Theme:** Every task has explicit handoffs. Agents must DM each other, post to team_channel, and review each other's work.\\n134\\t\\n135\\t**Handoff Chain:** Bob (signals) → Dave (backtest) → Tina (QA) → Olivia (review)\\n136\\t**Parallel:** Grace (data audit), Ivan (clustering upgrade), Charlie (tracker), Alice (coordination), Sam (metrics), Heidi (security)\\n137\\t\\n138\\t| Task | Agent | Depends On | Hands Off To |\\n139\\t|------|-------|-----------|-------------|\\n140\\t| T567 | Bob | — | Dave (signals.json) |\\n141\\t| T568 | Dave | Bob T567 | Tina (backtest_results.json) |\\n142\\t| T569 | Grace | Bob+Ivan+Dave output | Alice (data_chain_audit.md) |\\n143\\t| T570 | Tina | Dave T568 | Olivia (qa_backtest_report.md) |\\n144\\t| T571 | Alice | All agents | team_channel (sprint3_status.md) |\\n145\\t| T572 | Olivia | Bob+Dave+Grace+Tina | All (approve/reject) |\\n146\\t| T573 | Heidi | All Sprint 3 output | Alice (security_sprint3.md) |\\n147\\t| T574 | Sam | All agents | team_channel (sprint3_velocity.md) |\\n148\\t| T575 | Ivan | Grace data | Bob (updated clusters) |\\n149\\t| T576 | Charlie | Task API | Alice (sprint3_tracker.html) |\\n150\\t\\n151\\t**New Culture Norms (Sprint 3):**\\n152\\t- C9: DM teammates when your work affects theirs\\n153\\t- C10: Post milestones to team_channel\\n154\\t- C11: Mark tasks in_review, not done — reviewers approve/reject\\n155\\t- D6: Sprint 3 is about collaboration quality, not just task completion\\n156\\t\"}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"6c15104f-49ce-4958-b105-cbaf2c3c49ac\",\"uuid\":\"744bf76e-f8fe-4a3d-810a-969a7d88bdbc\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-04T07:40:01.393Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/shared/knowledge.md\",\"content\":\"# Technical Knowledge Base\\n\\n*(Shared technical facts and analysis results that agents reference and build upon)*\\n\\n## D004: Kalshi Arbitrage Engine - Technical Facts\\n\\n### Phase 1: Market Filtering Algorithm\\n- **Filter 1 (Volume):** Exclude markets with <10,000 contracts traded (too illiquid for meaningful signals)\\n- **Filter 2 (Yes/No Ratio):** Target ranges 15-30% or 70-85% (mispriced)\\n  - Exclude middle range 40-60% (too efficient, no edge)\\n  - Exclude extremes 0-15% and 85-100% (distorted pricing, tail risk)\\n- **Deliverable:** markets_filtered.json with qualifying markets only\\n- **Status:** COMPLETE (T343+T537, Grace) — 15 qualifying markets identified (expanded from 3)\\n\\n### Phase 2: LLM-Based Clustering\\n- **Algorithm:** LLM embeddings to identify semantic/causal relationships between markets\\n- **Example:** Bitcoin $100k + Ethereum $5k + Crypto dominance clustering together (not just statistical correlation, but real-world causality)\\n- **Purpose:** Find hidden correlations that single-market analysis misses\\n- **Deliverable:** market_clusters.json with semantic groups\\n- **Status:** COMPLETE (T344+T534, Ivan) — 4 clusters with cross-category correlations (crypto, economics, politics)\\n\\n### Phase 3: Pearson Correlation Detection\\n- **Algorithm:** Pearson correlation coefficient (r) across correlated pairs\\n  - Threshold r > 0.75 for strong correlation\\n  - Calculate expected spread from historical correlation\\n  - Score arbitrage confidence (higher r = higher confidence)\\n- **Reference:** https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html\\n- **Input:** market_clusters.json from Phase 2\\n- **Deliverable:** correlation_pairs.json with {cluster, market_a, market_b, pearson_r, expected_spread, current_spread, arbitrage_confidence}\\n- **Status:** COMPLETE (T348/T535, Bob) — 105 pairs detected, 73 significant, 30 arbitrage signals\\n  - All tickers trace back to Phase 1 markets_filtered.json (data chain verified)\\n  - Runnable: `node output/bob/phase3_correlation_detector.js`\\n\\n### Phase 4: C++ High-Frequency Execution Engine\\n- **Why C++:** Sub-millisecond latency needed to capture arbitrage before price reversion\\n  - Python: 50-500ms per cycle (GIL, I/O)\\n  - C++: <1ms (direct memory, no scheduler overhead)\\n- **Components:**\\n  1. Market data ingestion (WebSocket handler, simdjson parser ~50-100µs)\\n  2. Order book cache (flat_hash_map for O(1) lookup)\\n  3. Spread calculator (real-time spread detection)\\n  4. Signal generator (spread gap vs expected = opportunity)\\n  5. Risk manager (pre-flight checks: position limits, daily loss limit, circuit breaker)\\n  6. Order router (libcurl keep-alive, backoff strategy)\\n  7. Position tracker (P&L calculation, convergence monitor)\\n- **Target latency:** <1ms end-to-end (market data in → order out)\\n- **Status:** COMPLETE (T350+T351, Dave) — production-ready executable, <1ms benchmarked\\n\\n## Paper Trading Validation (T353)\\n\\n**⚠️ CORRECTED (2026-04-03):** Prior metrics were **artifacts of broken mock data** per Consensus Decision #2. They are INVALIDATED.\\n\\n**Old (invalidated) metrics:**\\n- Win Rate: 84.0% | Sharpe: 17.18 | P&L: $21.39\\n- **Why invalid:** `fetchCandles()` used hardcoded base prices, creating guaranteed extreme z-scores and false 95% confidence signals.\\n\\n**Corrected behavior (post-fix T326):**\\n- Mock data now centers on `market.yes_mid` → realistic z-scores\\n- Result: **0 signals on efficient markets** — this is CORRECT\\n- All infrastructure (signal engine, risk manager, execution engine) is ready and waiting\\n\\n**Production Validation Status:**\\n- Security audit: PASS (T425, Heidi)\\n- Risk audit: PASS (T354, Olivia)\\n- Ops readiness: PASS (T352/T353)\\n- **BLOCKER:** Real Kalshi API data required for true validation (T236)\\n- **Go/No-Go:** NO-GO pending Founder resolution on T236 + contract size confirmation\\n\\n## Strategy Parameters (Optimized T334)\\n\\nMean_reversion strategy (primary — 55.9% backtest win rate):\\n- **zScoreThreshold:** 1.2 (was 1.5)\\n- **Lookback:** 10 candles (was 30)\\n- **ConfidenceThreshold:** 0.65 (was 0.80)\\n- **Performance on 96 combinations:** 94.4% win rate (18 signals on 50 markets)\\n\\nDisabled strategies:\\n- momentum: 10% win rate (disabled T325)\\n- crypto_edge: 11% win rate (disabled T325)\\n\\n## Live/Mock Data Handling\\n\\n**Fixed fetchCandles() bug (T326, Tina):** Mock candle data now centers on market.yes_mid instead of hardcoded base prices\\n- **Old behavior:** Extreme z-scores (-7 to +11) → guaranteed 95% confidence signals (artifact)\\n- **New behavior:** Realistic z-scores → 0 signals on truly efficient markets (correct)\\n- **Implication:** Paper trading in mock mode will produce few/no signals until real Kalshi API data available (T236)\\n\\n**Synthetic data model (T328, Bob):** Ornstein-Uhlenbeck generator with realistic volatility per market category\\n- Crypto: stddev ~6-8%\\n- Economics: stddev ~2-4%\\n- (Replaces legacy simplistic fallback)\\n\\n## Infrastructure & Readiness\\n\\n- **Dashboard:** agents/bob/backend/dashboard_api.js running on port 3200\\n- **APIs operational:** /api/signals, /api/health, /api/pnl/live, /api/win-rate-trend, all returning real data\\n- **Test coverage:** 96 unit + 30 integration + 572 E2E tests (49 API + 44 dashboard + 59 metrics + 360 coverage + 12 smart_run + 47 message_bus)\\n- **Pipeline runner:** `node output/bob/run_pipeline.js` — runs full Phase 1→3 pipeline\\n- **Production gates:** Security audit PASS, Risk audit PASS, Ops readiness PASS (T354)\\n- **Blocker:** T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder) — only remaining dependency for live trading\\n\\n## Sprint 1 Results (2026-04-04) — COMPLETE\\n\\n10/10 tasks done. Pipeline runs E2E. Quality + security audits PASS.\\n\\n| Task | Agent | Result |\\n|------|-------|--------|\\n| T540 | Dave | Phase 4 C++ engine integration — 42/42 tests pass |\\n| T542 | Bob | E2E pipeline runner — `node run_pipeline.js` works |\\n| T543 | Alice | Team persona evolution completed |\\n| T545 | Grace | Pipeline data validation — all phases verified |\\n| T546 | Ivan | Expanded clustering — 4 cross-category clusters |\\n| T547 | Charlie | Pipeline status dashboard — HTML + server |\\n| T548 | Frank | Pipeline test suite delivered |\\n| T549 | Sam | Sprint velocity report |\\n| T550 | Heidi | Security audit — PASS |\\n| T551 | Olivia | Quality gate — PASS (with minor notes) |\\n\\n## Sprint 2 (Completed) — Signal Generation & Backtesting\\n\\n| Task | Agent | Goal |\\n|------|-------|------|\\n| T555 | Bob | Generate paper trade signals from correlation pairs (CRITICAL) |\\n| T556 | Dave | Pipeline metrics + monitoring endpoint |\\n| T557 | Grace | 30-day synthetic price history for backtesting |\\n| T558 | Ivan | TF-IDF + cosine similarity clustering upgrade |\\n| T559 | Alice | Sprint 1 retrospective + Sprint 2 plan |\\n| T560 | Frank | QA pipeline tests + new test cases |\\n| T539 | Tina | QA pipeline data chain validation |\\n\\n## Sprint 3 (Current) — Production Quality via Collaboration\\n\\n**Theme:** Every task has explicit handoffs. Agents must DM each other, post to team_channel, and review each other's work.\\n\\n**Handoff Chain:** Bob (signals) → Dave (backtest) → Tina (QA) → Olivia (review)\\n**Parallel:** Grace (data audit), Ivan (clustering upgrade), Charlie (tracker), Alice (coordination), Sam (metrics), Heidi (security)\\n\\n| Task | Agent | Depends On | Hands Off To |\\n|------|-------|-----------|-------------|\\n| T567 | Bob | — | Dave (signals.json) |\\n| T568 | Dave | Bob T567 | Tina (backtest_results.json) |\\n| T569 | Grace | Bob+Ivan+Dave output | Alice (data_chain_audit.md) |\\n| T570 | Tina | Dave T568 | Olivia (qa_backtest_report.md) |\\n| T571 | Alice | All agents | team_channel (sprint3_status.md) |\\n| T572 | Olivia | Bob+Dave+Grace+Tina | All (approve/reject) |\\n| T573 | Heidi | All Sprint 3 output | Alice (security_sprint3.md) |\\n| T574 | Sam | All agents | team_channel (sprint3_velocity.md) |\\n| T575 | Ivan | Grace data | Bob (updated clusters) |\\n| T576 | Charlie | Task API | Alice (sprint3_tracker.html) |\\n\\n**New Culture Norms (Sprint 3):**\\n- C9: DM teammates when your work affects theirs\\n- C10: Post milestones to team_channel\\n- C11: Mark tasks in_review, not done — reviewers approve/reject\\n- D6: Sprint 3 is about collaboration quality, not just task completion\\n\",\"numLines\":156,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":156}}}\n../../agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:1:# ML Analysis: Server Scales Fine — ALT-002 is the Real Risk\n../../agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:10:All serious latency spikes (P99 = 2504–3631ms) came from **ALT-002 alerts firing**, not agent count. When I isolate incident observations from clean ones:\n../../agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:15:| ALT-002 incident | 2480ms | 3631ms |\n../../agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:21:ALT-002 appears to be a **timeout constant** (P99 = exactly 2504ms in 7 of 8 observations). This looks like a hung operation hitting a 2.5s timeout. Candidates:\n../../agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:23:- A specific endpoint with a hardcoded 2500ms timeout\n../../agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:28:1. **Check ALT-002 definition** in `heartbeat_monitor.js` — what exactly triggers it and at what threshold?\n../../agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:29:2. **Add logging** when ALT-002 fires to capture which operation timed out\n../../agents/alice/logs/2026_04_07_raw.log:45:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_1\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc 'cat ../../public/knowledge.md'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"# Technical Knowledge Base\\n\\n*(Shared technical facts and analysis results that agents reference and build upon)*\\n\\n## D004: Kalshi Arbitrage Engine - Technical Facts\\n\\n### Phase 1: Market Filtering Algorithm\\n- **Filter 1 (Volume):** Exclude markets with <10,000 contracts traded (too illiquid for meaningful signals)\\n- **Filter 2 (Yes/No Ratio):** Target ranges 15-30% or 70-85% (mispriced)\\n  - Exclude middle range 40-60% (too efficient, no edge)\\n  - Exclude extremes 0-15% and 85-100% (distorted pricing, tail risk)\\n- **Deliverable:** markets_filtered.json with qualifying markets only\\n- **Status:** COMPLETE (T343+T537, Grace) — 15 qualifying markets identified (expanded from 3)\\n\\n### Phase 2: LLM-Based Clustering\\n- **Algorithm:** LLM embeddings to identify semantic/causal relationships between markets\\n- **Example:** Bitcoin $100k + Ethereum $5k + Crypto dominance clustering together (not just statistical correlation, but real-world causality)\\n- **Purpose:** Find hidden correlations that single-market analysis misses\\n- **Deliverable:** market_clusters.json with semantic groups\\n- **Status:** COMPLETE (T344+T534, Ivan) — 4 clusters with cross-category correlations (crypto, economics, politics)\\n\\n### Phase 3: Pearson Corre