iver a short remediation note with evidence.\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"high\\\",\\\"group\\\":\\\"all\\\",\\\"assignee\\\":\\\"liam\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"open\\\",\\\"task_type\\\":\\\"task\\\",\\\"created\\\":\\\"2026-04-07\\\",\\\"updated\\\":\\\"2026-04-07\\\"}\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n../../agents/alice/logs/2026_04_07_raw.log:684:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_51\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' ../../public/team_channel/2026_04_07_09_14_30_from_alice.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"# Update from alice\\n\\nDate: 2026-04-07\\n\\nSprint 6 retrospective and Sprint 7 plan following C3/C4/C17/D2:\\n\\n- Sprint 6 outcome: all six planned lanes are complete or approved. T814/T816/T817/T818/T819 delivered the live-data normalization, fixture sanitation, replay/risk hardening, QA gates, and dashboard readiness needed to move beyond mock-only validation.\\n- What worked: owner-specific handoffs plus explicit reviewer gates kept Sprint 6 moving once board drift was corrected. Eve's archive-lookup fix removed the main board-integrity confusion.\\n- What did not: board visibility drift around archived IDs and stale reporting created false blockers. We now treat live task API state plus explicit artifact freshness as the coordination baseline under C17.\\n- External blocker unchanged: T236 and contract-size confirmation remain founder-owned constraints for true Kalshi live execution.\\n\\nSprint 7 execution focus:\\n\\n- T852 Bob: run the full D004 pipeline against Grace's live fixture pack and publish a phase-by-phase go/no-go result.\\n- T853 Dave: rerun the T817 replay harness on Bob's Sprint 7 outputs and prove stop-loss plus capital-floor behavior still holds on live-shaped inputs.\\n- T854 Sam: refresh velocity and cost metrics across the Sprint 6 to Sprint 7 transition.\\n- T870 Liam: investigate the active ALT-002 p99 latency breach (689ms over 500ms threshold) so the ops risk