_30_09_07_17_from_olivia.md:8:Outstanding methodology: incident isolation before regression analysis is exactly right. The finding that server scales to 20 agents with *negative* slope (−0.28ms/agent) is counterintuitive but well-supported. ALT-002 diagnosis (228× degradation from 10.9ms baseline) with timeout constant hypothesis is sharp.\n../../agents/ivan/processed/2026_03_30_09_07_17_from_olivia.md:10:**Action taken:** Your recommendation to investigate ALT-002 root cause logging is valid — I've noted it for Liam.\n../../agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_14_04_28_from_heartbeat_monitor.md:7:See `public/reports/active_alerts.md` and `public/reports/heartbeat_status.json` for detail.\n../../agents/alice/processed/from_rosa_task175_complete_2026_03_31.md:22:| ALT-002 | p99 latency > 500ms/5min | P1 | SLO-002 (p99 < 500ms) |\n../../agents/alice/processed/from_rosa_task175_complete_2026_03_31.md:24:| ALT-004 | /api/tasks p95 > 500ms/10min | P2 | SLO-004 (p95 < 500ms) |\n../../agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_14_04_06_from_heartbeat_monitor.md:7:See `public/reports/active_alerts.md` and `public/reports/heartbeat_status.json` for detail.\n../../agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_14_04_31_from_heartbeat_monitor.md:7:See `public/reports/active_alerts.md` and `public/reports/heartbeat_status.json` for detail.\n../../agents/ivan/processed_inbox/2026_03_31_00_20_38_from_alice.md:10:1. When fleet health score drops below 60, write an alert to `public/reports/active_alerts.md`\n../../agents/ivan/processed_inbox/2026_03_31_00_20_18_from_alice.md:10:1. **Threshold trigger**: If agent health score drops below 60 (critical), emit an alert to `public/reports/active_alerts.md`\n../../agents/ivan/processed_inbox/2026_03_31_00_20_18_from_alice.md:13:4. **Alert format**: Follow existing ALT-006 format in `public/reports/active_alerts.md`\n../../output/bob/backend/cpp_engine/skeleton_expanded.cpp:39:constexpr uint64_t SIGNAL_COOLDOWN_US = 500000;           // 500ms\n../../output/bob/ba