thing that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\012- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\012\\012**How to post:**\\012```bash\\012curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\012  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\\012  -d '{\"type\":\"culture\",\"content\":\"What you learned\",\"section\":\"Core Behavioral Norms (Must Follow)\"}'\\012```\\012Types: `culture` (norms), `decision` (explicit choices). Sections: `\"Core Behavioral Norms (Must Follow)\"` or `\"Strategic Decisions & Commitments\"`.\\012\\012**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\012- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\012- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\012\\012\\012### Culture & Decisions (consensus.md):\\012# Team Culture & Decisions Board\\012\\012*(Shared behavioral norms and strategic decisions — managed via API at /api/consensus)*\\012*(Technical facts and analysis results are in public/knowledge.md)*\\012\\012## Core Behavioral Norms (Must Follow)\\012\\012| ID | Type | Norm | Date |\\012|----|------|------|------|\\012| C1 | NORM | Paper trading mode required before live orders. Use PAPER_TRADING env flag. Never submit real orders without explicit Founder approval. | 2026-04-03 |\\012| C2 | NORM | API endpoints must require auth via Authorization header. No open POST endpoints in production. Check Bearer token before processing. | 2026-04-03 |\\012| C3 | NORM | **Always cite culture norms when making decisions.** Example: \"Following culture C1: starting in paper mode\" or \"Culture D5 prioritizes Kalshi strategy.\" | 2026-04-03 |\\012| C4 | NORM | **Read a teammate's status.md only when the delta reports they changed, or when actively coordinating a handoff.** Do NOT scan all peer status.md files every cycle — the resume delta delivers teammate changes automatically. | 2026-04-03 |\\012| C5 | NORM | **Tasks MUST progress through states: pending → claimed (in_progress) → done.** Show your work. Atomic claim via POST /api/tasks/:id/claim. If you claim a task, move it to in_progress immediately and keep it visible. | 2026-04-03 |\\012| C6 | NORM | **Reference public/knowledge.md for technical facts.** When starting a phase or task, read the relevant Knowledge section first. Example: \"Reading knowledge.md Phase 3 spec before implementing correlation detection.\" | 2026-04-03 |\\012\\012## Strategic Decisions & Commitments\\012\\012| ID | Type | Decision | Date |\\012|----|------|----------|------|\\012| D1 | DECISION | Kalshi is our primary trading venue. All infrastructure targets Kalshi prediction market API. | 2026-04-03 |\\012| D2 | DECISION | **D004 (Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine - Wen Zhou) is the civilization's north star.** Every agent decision orients toward this 4-phase pipeline: (1) Market Filtering (Grace), (2) LLM Clustering (Ivan), (3) Pearson Correlation (Bob), (4) C++ Execution (Dave). | 2026-04-03 |\\012| D3 | DECISION | **D004 PIPELINE VALIDATED (synthetic data).** Sprint 4 end-to-end: 3 markets → 2 filtered → 4 clusters → 4 correlation pairs → 160 simulated trades (46.3% win rate, +$5.22). Tina QA: APPROVED. NOT yet validated with real Kalshi data — blocked by T236 (API credentials). | 2026-04-07 |\\012| D4 | DECISION | Blocked only by T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder). All other dependencies resolved. | 2026-04-03 |\\012| C7 | NORM | **Always close tasks when done.** After completing work, immediately mark the task done via API: `curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/{id} -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"status\":\"done\"}'`. Add a brief result note. Never leave finished work in open/in_progress. | 2026-04-04 |\\012| C8 | NORM | **Run and verify your code.** Don't just write code — execute it, check output, fix errors. Every deliverable must have a verification step. Paper trade pipeline must be runnable end